# NxtHealth — Frozen Decisions Reference

*This document contains only finalized/frozen decisions. Update only when a new decision is explicitly frozen — do not add speculative or pending items.*

---

## PROJECT

**Name:** NxtHealth
**Tagline:** Your trusted guide for your next healthcare decision.
**Pitch:** Explainable healthcare decision-support platform for before/during/after treatment. Every output answers Why? Why not? Alternatives? Trade-offs? Confidence/limitations.
**Hard constraint:** NOT an AI doctor, symptom checker, or disease predictor. No module output may read as diagnostic or predictive.
**Build constraints:** Solo dev, 2-3 day hackathon, polished not just MVP. Free/open-source only (no paid APIs/DBs/auth/OCR). Built from GitHub starter templates. Fewer moving parts beats more.

---

## THE SIX MODULES

1. **Insurance/Policy Advisor** (top priority, primary USP) — profile matched against curated policy DB. AI explains why/why-not/trade-off; never invents a policy. Graceful no-match handling. Stateless beyond profile.
2. **Preventive Health Planner** (#2) — profile → advice tied to a specific stated reason, never generic tips. Stateless beyond profile.
3. **Generic Medicine Alternatives** (#3) — DB lookup only, never AI-generated. "Not available" if no match. Stateless.
4 & 5. **Term / Prescription Explainer** (combined) — one module, `context` flag (`term`/`prescription`) adjusts prompt. Plain-language comprehension aid only. Stateless.
6. **Recovery Guidance** (lowest priority) — manual schedule: medicine timeline, test dates, report hand-off. Only module with persisted state (`recovery_items`). One active plan per user, no history/auto-fill.

**History feature: dropped entirely.** No per-search logs anywhere. Recovery Guidance's data is forward-looking state, not a log.

**Central profile:** one row per user (`profiles`), filled progressively, user-editable, source of truth (not a hidden cache).

**Input-handling rule (platform-wide):** any field mapped to a real data boundary = dropdown/constrained range, never free text. Exception: Term/Prescription Explainer free-text input (no DB boundary exists there).

---

## TECH STACK

Next.js (Vercel) + Node/Express (Render, separate service) + Supabase Postgres (JSONB profile + relational policy tables) + Supabase Auth + Gemini API (Flash/Flash-Lite only). One GitHub monorepo: `/frontend` + `/backend`. Cold-start mitigation: ping backend on page load + spinner on first backend-triggering action. Gemini free tier may be used by Google to train — avoid highly sensitive data if that becomes a concern. Code split ~65% frontend / 35% backend.

