Note: `min_entry_age`, `max_entry_age`, `ped_waiting_months`, `max_dependents` are `numeric`, not `integer` — source CSV exported whole numbers as floats (e.g. `99.0`), numeric was chosen over re-cleaning the file.

**policy_details** (1:1 via `policy_id` FK → `policies.id`) — **LIVE in Supabase, 42 rows imported.**
entry_age_description, premium_description, room_rent_capping_rules, maternity_benefit_details, restoration_benefit_rules, opd_coverage_details, consumables_cover_status, air_ambulance_global_cover, copay_percentage (text), network_hospital_tier, claim_settlement_ratio_percentage (text), no_claim_bonus_structure, annual_health_checkup_terms, pre_post_hospitalization_days, teleconsultation_digital_perks, organ_donor_expenses_rules. Verbatim rich text, unmodified from source — never cleaned/normalized, fed to AI as-is.

**medicines** (reference/static) — **table created in Supabase; CSV cleaned, import in progress.**
id (serial, auto-generated — source CSV has no natural ID), medicine_name, brand_manufacturer, active_ingredient (not null — highest-stakes field, still unverified against 1mg/PharmEasy/Jan Aushadhi), drug_class, common_use_case, generic_alternative_names, generic_manufacturers_examples, estimated_brand_price_inr (text — range + unit, not clean numeric), estimated_generic_price_inr (text, same reason), price_difference_note, dosage_form, needs_manual_verification (boolean), verification_note (text — split out from source's combined YES/NO+reason field).

**profiles** (id = auth.users.id) — not yet built. identity (jsonb), lifestyle (jsonb), medical (jsonb), created_at, updated_at. Three separate jsonb columns to prevent concurrent-write clobbering.
- **identity** (must-have): name, age, gender, city, budget_band, marital_status, kids_count
- **lifestyle**: height_cm*, weight_kg* (must-have); smoking_status, alcohol_consumption, exercise_frequency, dietary_preference, sleep_hours_avg (good-to-have)
