## MATCHING LOGIC — INSURANCE ADVISOR

`city_tier` = literal `"Both"` on every current row (matches any user city). Wildcard behavior identical to originally-planned `"All Cities"` value, just renamed for consistency with frontend enum.

**Step 1 — hard SQL filter:** age BETWEEN min/max_entry_age; city match; kids_count ≤ max_dependents; budget checked against correct age-bracket premium columns. `needs_manual_review=true` policies included but flagged downstream.

**Step 2 — cascading fallback** (only if Step 1 returns zero rows; age & city_tier never relaxed):
1. Soft budget extend (×1.10, never shown as raw number — surfaced as "slightly above your selected budget")
2. Query A — drop budget_band
3. Query B — drop kids_count/max_dependents
4. Query C — drop both

Merge + dedupe by policy_id, keep smallest-relaxation tag (priority: soft-extend > A > B > C). Zero rows after Query C = honest "no good match" empty state.

**Step 3 — single Gemini call:** full tagged candidate set + profile + policy_details → ranks top 3, explains why/why-not/trade-off, incorporates relaxation tag + manual-review caveat. AI never determines eligibility, only ranks/explains within the SQL-determined set.

