## API CONTRACT

**Direct-to-Supabase** (pure CRUD, RLS-protected, no backend needed): profile read/write, recovery_items CRUD, medicine alternatives lookup.
**Render (Express) endpoints:** `POST /api/insurance-advisor`, `POST /api/preventive-planner`, `POST /api/term-explainer`

**Profile-data trust model (accepted trade-off):** frontend sends profile data directly in request body; Render doesn't re-fetch server-side. Accepted as low-risk for hackathon-demo scope only.

**Error handling:** ok/no_match → HTTP 200 `{status, results}`. Genuine failures (timeout, malformed response) → HTTP 500 `{status:"error", message}`.

**CORS:** Express `cors` package, allow deployed Vercel domain + localhost:3000, configured from day one of local dev.

**Deployment:** minimal skeleton (static Express route + near-blank Next.js page) deployed to Render + Vercel early, before real module logic, to surface cold-start/CORS/env-var issues early.

