## RLS & DATA SAFETY

RLS mandatory on `profiles` and `recovery_items` (restrict to `auth.uid()`) — non-negotiable given data sensitivity, not yet implemented (auth not yet built). `policies`, `policy_details`, `medicines` are public reference data — no RLS needed, currently open on anon key by default (acceptable pre-launch, must not ship with write access open). `recovery_items.user_id` indexed manually (FKs aren't auto-indexed by Supabase). New jsonb field = no migration. New module later = one new table + its own RLS policy.

