## UI/UX DECISIONS (frozen)

1. **Checklist mutual exclusivity:** disable-on-select (see Vocabulary section above).
2. **Recovery Guidance entry UX:** three separate purpose-built entry flows — "+ Add Medicine" (dosage, frequency, start date, end date), "+ Add Test" (test name, date), "+ Add Reminder" (report hand-off, date). All items feed into one unified list/timeline, sorted by `scheduled_date`, regardless of type.
3. **Explanation card rendering:** accordion per result. `explanation` expanded by default. `why_not`/`alternatives`/`trade_offs` shown as labeled, expandable sections (e.g. "Why not this one?") — not hidden behind a vague "more" link. Null fields render no section at all.

